 will familiarize you with the basic terms and key concepts. And if you are taking an undergraduate stylistics course and you need help on analyzing texts, you will find here a step-by-step guide to analyzing different text types using a defined selection of stylistic frameworks. You will be introduced to the analysis of poetry, fiction, drama, humorous writing, advertising, political texts and online journalism and offered guided practice in a range of methodologies, with a particular focus on functional and pragmatic stylistics. The opening chapter introduces you to the key foundational terms and concepts, covering dialect, register, field, tenor, mode, choice, deviation, and foregrounding. The remaining chapters guide you from theory into practice. Each stylistic analysis chapter starts with a summary of the methodological toolkit that will be used, followed by systematic and guided stylistic analysis of a particular text type and plenty of practice activities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish languagexStyle. 0aLanguage and languagesxStyle. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Pragmatics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447718540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474477185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474477185/original  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles